news_header: Swedish forests are believed to be a stronger carbon sink than those in Finland. The Swedish parliamentary body, Miljömålsberedningen, assesses that Sweden is not meeting EU climate targets, with some members calling the goals unattainable.
news_original_title: Arviointiryhmä: Ruotsin metsien ilmastotavoitteita mahdoton saavuttaa
news_text: The Swedish Environment Agency reported that the carbon sink should increase by 19 million tonnes by 2030, but evaluators claim this is impossible due to slowed forest growth and increased logging. Some believe the targets can still be met with political will.
